0
00:00:06,239 --> 00:00:09,072
Feb. 12, 1912

1
00:00:09,142 --> 00:00:11,076
second year of the Revolution.

2
00:00:11,144 --> 00:00:14,136
An edict proclaimed

3
00:00:14,247 --> 00:00:16,010
the abdication of Emperor Pu Yi.

4
00:00:16,049 --> 00:00:20,008
And the end of the Manchu Dynasty.

5
00:00:20,086 --> 00:00:22,179
A new China was in the offing.

6
00:00:22,222 --> 00:00:27,057
Many, however failed to cope.

7
00:00:27,227 --> 00:00:30,060
Eunuchs, for instance.

8
00:00:30,296 --> 00:00:33,265
Grand their titles might be.

9
00:00:34,034 --> 00:00:37,162
They were in fact royal slaves.

10
00:00:37,237 --> 00:00:39,262
Castration is the eunuch's prerequisite.

11
00:00:40,006 --> 00:00:42,998
That means the removal of male genitals.

12
00:00:43,076 --> 00:00:45,067
The eunuchs down the centuries

13
00:00:45,145 --> 00:00:49,138
called fondly the cut off part as Pet.

14
00:00:49,282 --> 00:00:53,082
The Pet was boiled in oil and wrapped

15
00:00:53,153 --> 00:00:57,021
put in a container and
suspended in midair

16
00:00:57,123 --> 00:01:00,991
The eunuchs invariably
came from poor families.

17
00:01:01,061 --> 00:01:04,997
They were forced
onto this path of no return.

18
00:01:59,085 --> 00:02:07,117
One, two, one, two...

19
00:02:10,296 --> 00:02:12,127
Hurry up.

20
00:02:12,165 --> 00:02:15,225
Wait for me.

21
00:02:17,237 --> 00:02:19,171
- Laishi.
- Yes.

22
00:02:21,174 --> 00:02:23,005
Yes, Master Eunuch.

23
00:02:23,076 --> 00:02:25,237
- Get me that flower.
- Yes.

24
00:02:26,045 --> 00:02:33,144
Hurry up.

25
00:02:36,156 --> 00:02:39,182
Hurry up, you stupid.

26
00:02:40,059 --> 00:02:42,254
- Get him.
- Yes.

27
00:02:49,135 --> 00:02:51,035
Tsouti.

28
00:02:58,178 --> 00:03:00,043
Take it.

29
00:03:19,032 --> 00:03:19,999
Young Teh Chang is here.

30
00:03:20,099 --> 00:03:22,260
Laishi, come over here.

31
00:03:31,077 --> 00:03:32,169
Who's that?

32
00:03:32,212 --> 00:03:35,113
- It's Young Teh Chang
- Young Teh Chang?

33
00:03:45,291 --> 00:03:47,225
Don't take those with bones.

34
00:03:53,199 --> 00:03:58,159
Yummy, yummy.

35
00:03:58,304 --> 00:04:01,102
Don't, these kids are so pitiful.

36
00:04:01,174 --> 00:04:03,233
Don't dump it on the ground.

37
00:04:03,309 --> 00:04:07,143
Lord Chang is right, they are pitiable.

38
00:04:07,213 --> 00:04:10,148
Leave it in the barrel for them.

39
00:04:10,183 --> 00:04:12,048
Let's go.

40
00:04:16,089 --> 00:04:17,215
Go, go.

41
00:04:20,159 --> 00:04:22,024
One more barrel there.

42
00:04:35,074 --> 00:04:36,132
Dad.

43
00:04:37,176 --> 00:04:39,076
Bye.

44
00:04:39,145 --> 00:04:42,137
The emperor is easier
to please than she is.

45
00:04:42,215 --> 00:04:43,239
I want to have my thing snipped.

46
00:04:44,183 --> 00:04:46,048
Nonsense.

47
00:04:46,319 --> 00:04:48,082
I want to serve the emperor.

48
00:04:48,121 --> 00:04:50,180
Then I'd have shoes to wear.

49
00:04:50,256 --> 00:04:53,020
It's a chicken bottom.

50
00:04:58,031 --> 00:05:00,226
Really? Let me have a sniff.

51
00:05:01,267 --> 00:05:03,098
I'll split it in two.

52
00:05:03,169 --> 00:05:05,262
No need, you have it all.

53
00:05:06,005 --> 00:05:08,166
When can I have my thing snipped?

54
00:05:09,242 --> 00:05:11,107
Ask your mother.

55
00:05:11,277 --> 00:05:13,142
If she says yes, then it's alright.

56
00:05:14,180 --> 00:05:17,047
Go, go.

57
00:05:20,286 --> 00:05:22,117
Really?

58
00:05:22,155 --> 00:05:23,247
Yes.

59
00:05:25,058 --> 00:05:26,116
Really?

60
00:05:26,259 --> 00:05:28,159
Yes.

61
00:05:40,273 --> 00:05:42,138
Chiang Fu.

62
00:05:48,081 --> 00:05:49,275
Good morning, sir.

63
00:05:50,283 --> 00:05:54,014
I'm not here for the rent.

64
00:05:54,087 --> 00:05:56,282
I'm here for a favour.

65
00:05:58,124 --> 00:06:00,217
- Are you crazy?
- Don't hit me.

66
00:06:00,293 --> 00:06:02,158
- You are out of your mind.
- I wouldn't dare anymore.

67
00:06:02,261 --> 00:06:05,094
Get lost and don't come back.

68
00:06:14,307 --> 00:06:16,275
You did him a favour, what about us?

69
00:06:17,043 --> 00:06:18,169
But he said...

70
00:06:18,211 --> 00:06:20,202
And you had to offer him all our food.

71
00:06:20,279 --> 00:06:23,043
How do we carry on?

72
00:06:23,116 --> 00:06:24,276
He said the emperor's in trouble.

73
00:06:25,017 --> 00:06:28,282
We're in trouble too, and who cares?

74
00:06:31,057 --> 00:06:33,252
I'm going, you go to your emperor.

75
00:06:34,060 --> 00:06:37,188
The emperor protects us from foreigners.

76
00:06:38,197 --> 00:06:40,131
And the revolutionaries.

77
00:06:40,299 --> 00:06:42,096
Who'll take care of us
if the emperor's dead?

78
00:06:42,168 --> 00:06:44,033
Great, great.

79
00:06:44,137 --> 00:06:45,195
Come here.

80
00:06:49,108 --> 00:06:50,166
Go.

81
00:06:56,249 --> 00:06:59,013
Don't go.

82
00:06:59,085 --> 00:07:00,245
Who's going to cook for us?

83
00:07:01,020 --> 00:07:02,180
Cooking with what?

84
00:07:02,255 --> 00:07:04,052
I'm going to dig up some roots.

85
00:07:04,123 --> 00:07:05,112
Dig up some roots?

86
00:07:05,191 --> 00:07:06,180
Come here, Laishi.

87
00:07:06,259 --> 00:07:08,124
What for?

88
00:07:11,030 --> 00:07:12,156
Mesh roots again?

89
00:07:12,231 --> 00:07:16,031
Aren't you tired of it yet?

90
00:07:21,174 --> 00:07:22,266
Aren't you going?

91
00:07:25,211 --> 00:07:28,078
I'm going to borrow some rice.

92
00:07:31,184 --> 00:07:34,051
Great, rice for dinner.

93
00:07:34,120 --> 00:07:37,214
Mum's here can't do it now.

94
00:07:37,290 --> 00:07:40,054
No more chicken bottoms.

95
00:07:40,126 --> 00:07:42,219
- What now?
- Send her away.

96
00:07:43,029 --> 00:07:45,054
Don't you want some chicken bottoms?

97
00:07:45,097 --> 00:07:46,223
Think of something.

98
00:07:50,236 --> 00:07:51,225
Why are you throwing things at me?

99
00:07:51,304 --> 00:07:54,171
How dare you.

100
00:07:55,041 --> 00:07:58,135
You feel ashamed that I'm borrowing.

101
00:07:59,212 --> 00:08:02,147
Send her away, dad.

102
00:08:02,215 --> 00:08:03,182
I'm a man.

103
00:08:03,282 --> 00:08:07,048
I won't beg for food.

104
00:08:07,119 --> 00:08:08,211
Get away.

105
00:08:17,230 --> 00:08:19,095
Come with me.

106
00:08:21,234 --> 00:08:23,065
Laishi.

107
00:08:27,073 --> 00:08:28,233
I'm a man too.

108
00:08:29,041 --> 00:08:30,099
Good.

109
00:08:32,211 --> 00:08:33,269
Dad.

110
00:08:45,191 --> 00:08:47,022
Dad, where are you going?

111
00:08:47,126 --> 00:08:48,150
To find your mother.

112
00:08:48,194 --> 00:08:50,094
Snip it off before you do that.

113
00:08:50,162 --> 00:08:52,255
Sit down, dad.

114
00:08:52,298 --> 00:08:55,233
Everything's alright after I snip it off.

115
00:08:55,301 --> 00:08:58,168
Mum won't be mad at you again.

116
00:08:59,272 --> 00:09:02,264
Dad, I'm a man, I'll be the first.

117
00:09:18,057 --> 00:09:19,183
Take care of your sister.

118
00:09:19,258 --> 00:09:22,022
District Chief.

119
00:09:22,194 --> 00:09:23,218
What happened in town?

120
00:09:23,296 --> 00:09:25,093
Good news, the emperor is out.

121
00:09:25,164 --> 00:09:27,029
The revolutionaries won.

122
00:09:27,099 --> 00:09:28,191
Is that right?

123
00:09:30,069 --> 00:09:31,263
Who'll be the new emperor?

124
00:09:32,038 --> 00:09:35,007
Don't know.
But no more pig-tails for sure.

125
00:09:46,152 --> 00:09:48,245
What's there, dad?

126
00:09:49,088 --> 00:09:51,249
Wax, goose down, calcium powder, chili.

127
00:09:51,290 --> 00:09:53,019
What for?

128
00:09:53,092 --> 00:09:57,028
To stop bleeding, according to grandpa.

129
00:09:57,129 --> 00:09:58,153
To snip off how much?

130
00:09:58,230 --> 00:09:59,219
Whatever is there.

131
00:09:59,298 --> 00:10:01,129
You'll be just like your sister.

132
00:10:02,301 --> 00:10:04,235
Have you got what I told you to get?

133
00:10:07,139 --> 00:10:08,265
What's that?

134
00:10:09,275 --> 00:10:11,072
For chopping off heads?

135
00:10:11,143 --> 00:10:12,269
Death penalty for keeping a pig-tail?

136
00:10:13,012 --> 00:10:14,980
Up to the Government.

137
00:10:15,081 --> 00:10:16,207
So is it the death penalty or not?

138
00:10:16,282 --> 00:10:18,182
No one mentioned anything yet.

139
00:10:26,125 --> 00:10:28,252
It's bloody sharp.

140
00:10:29,028 --> 00:10:30,154
Ready.

141
00:10:31,030 --> 00:10:32,054
Yes.

142
00:10:34,100 --> 00:10:35,260
I'm going to do it.

143
00:10:36,035 --> 00:10:37,093
Come on.

144
00:10:40,106 --> 00:10:41,073
For real now.

145
00:10:41,173 --> 00:10:42,105
No, no way.

146
00:10:42,174 --> 00:10:43,198
It's like castration.

147
00:10:43,309 --> 00:10:46,210
- Who's going to be emperor?
- Don't know.

148
00:10:46,245 --> 00:10:48,076
Come on.

149
00:11:19,178 --> 00:11:22,079
Mum, mum.

150
00:11:24,216 --> 00:11:29,279
Mum, am I the first one?

151
00:11:31,123 --> 00:11:35,253
It hurts, mum. I want to pee.

152
00:11:36,128 --> 00:11:39,188
Don't move, it hasn't healed yet.

153
00:11:39,198 --> 00:11:42,065
You must sleep for 100 days.

154
00:11:42,101 --> 00:11:43,193
Good boy.

155
00:11:43,302 --> 00:11:46,271
I want to pee.

156
00:12:04,056 --> 00:12:08,015
Must change a new feather after peeling.

157
00:12:08,127 --> 00:12:10,152
Must change everyday.

158
00:12:11,097 --> 00:12:17,002
Or else you have to pee with your nose.

159
00:12:21,173 --> 00:12:23,038
Good boy.

160
00:12:31,050 --> 00:12:32,142
I have the answer.

161
00:12:35,221 --> 00:12:36,210
Yes?

162
00:12:36,288 --> 00:12:40,088
Must fry in oil, and wrap after dry.

163
00:12:40,192 --> 00:12:42,023
I've borrowed some oil.

164
00:12:42,061 --> 00:12:43,153
So go ahead.

165
00:12:43,229 --> 00:12:45,197
I have to change the medicine.

166
00:12:45,264 --> 00:12:46,993
Where's the thing?

167
00:12:47,066 --> 00:12:49,000
In the bowl.

168
00:12:59,278 --> 00:13:02,008
What are you waiting for?

169
00:13:02,047 --> 00:13:04,277
I've forgot to get the recipe.

170
00:13:05,050 --> 00:13:08,281
Never mind, use a large fire.

171
00:13:09,054 --> 00:13:10,248
He has to keep it for lift.

172
00:13:11,056 --> 00:13:14,082
Has to be well done.

173
00:13:23,102 --> 00:13:27,004
It's late, go home please.

174
00:13:27,072 --> 00:13:30,235
Go home, weather's getting cold.

175
00:13:31,043 --> 00:13:33,068
Go now.

176
00:13:41,187 --> 00:13:43,052
Don't catch cold.

177
00:13:44,190 --> 00:13:47,091
Your son is the last eunuch
of Ching Dynasty.

178
00:13:47,159 --> 00:13:50,060
Come out, Laishi, Master Eunuch.

179
00:13:50,229 --> 00:13:52,060
Shut up you scum. Shut up.

180
00:13:52,097 --> 00:13:56,033
Or you'll be cursed.

181
00:14:20,092 --> 00:14:21,059
Where's the thing?

182
00:14:21,160 --> 00:14:23,219
It's in the bag.

183
00:14:29,201 --> 00:14:35,140
Keep it even into the coffin with you.

184
00:14:35,174 --> 00:14:39,076
Or you won't be a man in the next life.

185
00:14:39,144 --> 00:14:40,111
Yes.

186
00:14:40,179 --> 00:14:41,271
Don't lose it.

187
00:14:42,281 --> 00:14:44,181
I shall return in a sedan.

188
00:14:44,250 --> 00:14:47,219
And there'll be a lot of chicken bottoms.

189
00:14:49,154 --> 00:14:51,019
Good boy.

190
00:14:52,224 --> 00:14:54,055
Go.

191
00:14:54,193 --> 00:14:55,285
We are going.

192
00:14:59,265 --> 00:15:03,099
Any Masters of my age, dad?

193
00:15:04,003 --> 00:15:05,231
The emperor doesn't need eunuchs anymore.

194
00:15:06,038 --> 00:15:09,997
The emperor will
win back his throne soon.

195
00:15:10,042 --> 00:15:11,168
Then you'll be a eunuch.

196
00:15:11,243 --> 00:15:13,074
When?

197
00:15:14,046 --> 00:15:18,176
You must try to learn from the troupe.

198
00:15:22,054 --> 00:15:23,180
Alright.

199
00:15:42,274 --> 00:15:44,139
Stop.

200
00:15:44,310 --> 00:15:46,107
Laishi.

201
00:15:46,312 --> 00:15:49,008
You're supposed to be a drunken empress.

202
00:15:49,081 --> 00:15:52,312
Not a prostitute on the loose.

203
00:15:53,052 --> 00:15:57,113
An empress speaks elegantly.

204
00:15:57,156 --> 00:16:00,091
Sways like a willow when drunk.

205
00:16:00,192 --> 00:16:02,023
Not clumsy like you.

206
00:16:02,094 --> 00:16:05,154
Who wants an emperor like you?

207
00:16:05,264 --> 00:16:08,062
Let me show you.

208
00:16:08,133 --> 00:16:11,034
It was my favourite role.

209
00:16:11,103 --> 00:16:14,129
I'd do it myself if I were slimmer.

210
00:16:14,206 --> 00:16:17,107
Take this drunken scene.

211
00:16:20,279 --> 00:16:22,144
Feel good.

212
00:16:27,286 --> 00:16:29,151
What's that?

213
00:16:30,022 --> 00:16:31,216
Smell so good.

214
00:16:31,290 --> 00:16:35,090
Oh? A flower.

215
00:16:35,160 --> 00:16:39,256
Let me put it in my hair.

216
00:16:40,032 --> 00:16:42,227
Must be pretty.

217
00:16:43,235 --> 00:16:46,227
I'll take a closer look.

218
00:16:52,177 --> 00:16:54,202
Smell so good.

219
00:16:54,279 --> 00:16:57,976
What kind of a flower?

220
00:17:04,123 --> 00:17:06,216
- Got it.
- Yes.

221
00:17:06,291 --> 00:17:08,282
Then come pick me up.

222
00:17:29,181 --> 00:17:34,084
Good.

223
00:17:36,121 --> 00:17:38,021
Have a bite, General.

224
00:17:38,090 --> 00:17:39,250
Eat it yourself.

225
00:17:50,102 --> 00:17:55,005
Good.

226
00:18:14,259 --> 00:18:17,023
Bring him to me tomorrow.

227
00:18:17,129 --> 00:18:18,118
Yes.

228
00:18:22,067 --> 00:18:23,159
Master.

229
00:18:25,137 --> 00:18:26,069
Boss.

230
00:18:26,171 --> 00:18:28,230
Have a seat, master.

231
00:18:29,241 --> 00:18:31,209
- Good response
- Really?

232
00:18:31,276 --> 00:18:34,177
Not necessary for you.

233
00:18:34,279 --> 00:18:36,076
Yes.

234
00:18:37,015 --> 00:18:38,175
Anything for your folks.

235
00:18:38,250 --> 00:18:39,239
Someone's going that way.

236
00:18:39,284 --> 00:18:41,081
Yes, there is.

237
00:18:47,159 --> 00:18:48,251
3, 4, 5, 6.

238
00:18:48,293 --> 00:18:52,059
Are you on the run or what?

239
00:18:53,165 --> 00:18:56,225
Will you ask the person to take these?

240
00:18:56,301 --> 00:18:58,030
Alright.

241
00:18:58,070 --> 00:19:01,039
At least get a new pair of shoes.

242
00:19:01,206 --> 00:19:03,140
I like the old ones.

243
00:19:06,278 --> 00:19:09,008
Go get a new pair tomorrow.

244
00:19:09,081 --> 00:19:10,275
Thank you, master.

245
00:19:11,083 --> 00:19:13,017
Take this to my folks please.

246
00:19:13,118 --> 00:19:14,176
Go buy the shoes.

247
00:19:14,219 --> 00:19:17,017
I buy a pair when I get paid.

248
00:19:17,089 --> 00:19:18,249
The old ones are still good.

249
00:19:20,159 --> 00:19:22,059
Never mind then.

250
00:19:23,128 --> 00:19:24,254
Master, master.

251
00:19:25,063 --> 00:19:26,052
What? Want it back?

252
00:19:26,131 --> 00:19:29,999
No. Any news?

253
00:19:32,037 --> 00:19:33,163
How long have you been with me?

254
00:19:33,205 --> 00:19:34,194
9 years.

255
00:19:34,273 --> 00:19:36,104
No, more like 10.

256
00:19:36,141 --> 00:19:37,267
Aren't you well fed and well treated?

257
00:19:38,043 --> 00:19:39,101
Haven't I taught you everything?

258
00:19:39,178 --> 00:19:41,043
Yes, yes.

259
00:19:42,014 --> 00:19:45,177
But it's chao outside.

260
00:19:45,217 --> 00:19:48,209
The emperor is our true leader.

261
00:19:49,221 --> 00:19:51,018
He needs to be served.

262
00:19:51,123 --> 00:19:52,112
Don't I need to be served?

263
00:19:52,191 --> 00:19:53,180
Of course.

264
00:19:53,258 --> 00:19:55,055
But?

265
00:19:56,028 --> 00:19:58,189
Please come over here.

266
00:20:01,233 --> 00:20:04,031
I'm a eunuch, eunuchs stay in the Palace.

267
00:20:04,069 --> 00:20:05,093
What's so special about being a eunuch?

268
00:20:05,170 --> 00:20:06,159
You can work like anybody.

269
00:20:06,271 --> 00:20:07,260
Right?

270
00:20:08,006 --> 00:20:09,132
Why bother that monkey of a man?

271
00:20:13,212 --> 00:20:15,271
But I'm castrated.

272
00:20:16,114 --> 00:20:18,105
I can say I'm castrated too.

273
00:20:18,150 --> 00:20:20,141
Can you prove I'm not?

274
00:20:21,086 --> 00:20:24,021
I can say anything.

275
00:20:24,089 --> 00:20:26,990
Like I have 3 belly buttons,
who can tell.

276
00:20:27,059 --> 00:20:29,118
As long as you keep your clothes on.

277
00:20:29,194 --> 00:20:31,025
Who can tell the difference?

278
00:20:32,030 --> 00:20:33,258
No eunuchs have been hired
for a while now.

279
00:20:34,099 --> 00:20:36,226
Unless the old ones are dying.

280
00:20:36,268 --> 00:20:38,099
And need some money.

281
00:20:38,170 --> 00:20:42,038
But then it costs 60 coins to fill in.

282
00:20:42,174 --> 00:20:43,163
But...

283
00:20:43,242 --> 00:20:47,110
Your future is here.

284
00:20:47,179 --> 00:20:49,044
Stop being silly.

285
00:20:49,114 --> 00:20:50,138
- Master
- Alright...

286
00:20:50,215 --> 00:20:52,115
I know... Alright...

287
00:20:52,184 --> 00:20:54,049
Master.

288
00:21:06,198 --> 00:21:08,132
Where's the kid?

289
00:21:08,200 --> 00:21:11,135
Let's go to the girls.

290
00:21:11,203 --> 00:21:14,001
I don't have time, may be next time.

291
00:21:14,273 --> 00:21:16,173
Hey, kid.

292
00:21:16,241 --> 00:21:19,108
Only eunuchs are afraid to go in.

293
00:21:19,144 --> 00:21:21,078
Let's check it out.

294
00:21:21,179 --> 00:21:23,079
The rebel gets lost in the whore houses.

295
00:21:23,148 --> 00:21:25,173
Get him, hurry.

296
00:21:26,084 --> 00:21:33,081
Go in, go in.

297
00:21:35,160 --> 00:21:36,991
Open up.

298
00:21:38,030 --> 00:21:39,190
Open up.

299
00:21:57,049 --> 00:21:58,243
Are you scared?

300
00:21:59,251 --> 00:22:03,085
You won't be scared in a minute.

301
00:22:03,188 --> 00:22:05,019
I have no money.

302
00:22:06,058 --> 00:22:08,026
It's paid for.

303
00:22:10,028 --> 00:22:12,087
- Come on.
- No.

304
00:22:17,069 --> 00:22:18,969
Come out.

305
00:22:19,137 --> 00:22:20,263
Damn.

306
00:22:25,210 --> 00:22:27,110
You will see when I get you.

307
00:23:08,019 --> 00:23:10,010
It's all quiet.

308
00:23:20,198 --> 00:23:22,166
They are your friends?

309
00:23:27,239 --> 00:23:29,070
Thank you.

310
00:23:32,244 --> 00:23:34,178
How come you...

311
00:23:35,180 --> 00:23:38,047
...you are in this business?

312
00:23:38,150 --> 00:23:39,139
It would have been different.

313
00:23:39,217 --> 00:23:41,082
If you had your way.

314
00:23:41,119 --> 00:23:42,211
But...

315
00:23:55,233 --> 00:23:56,222
Feel good.

316
00:23:57,002 --> 00:23:59,095
Help! Soo, open up.

317
00:23:59,171 --> 00:24:01,036
Stop running, you trash.

318
00:24:01,072 --> 00:24:02,096
Open up, Sister Soo.

319
00:24:02,174 --> 00:24:06,076
Help, open up.

320
00:24:06,211 --> 00:24:08,076
Come out, you trash.

321
00:24:08,146 --> 00:24:10,205
I'm not going to sleep with that fatso.

322
00:24:10,282 --> 00:24:13,046
Give your mum a break.

323
00:24:13,084 --> 00:24:14,244
He's here, and he has paid.

324
00:24:14,319 --> 00:24:16,116
What am I going to do?

325
00:24:16,188 --> 00:24:18,019
You asked him here, and he paid you.

326
00:24:18,056 --> 00:24:21,025
You sleep with him.

327
00:24:21,092 --> 00:24:22,024
I'll show you.

328
00:24:22,127 --> 00:24:23,185
You trash.

329
00:24:23,228 --> 00:24:24,160
What did you say?

330
00:24:24,262 --> 00:24:25,194
- Don't come near.
- What did you say?

331
00:24:27,098 --> 00:24:28,224
How much did that fatso pay?

332
00:24:28,300 --> 00:24:31,235
This kid will fill in for him.

333
00:24:32,037 --> 00:24:35,165
Don't kid me.

334
00:24:35,240 --> 00:24:37,140
She's in no condition to work, look.

335
00:24:37,209 --> 00:24:40,042
I'll fill in for her.

336
00:24:40,111 --> 00:24:42,170
Not a penny less.

337
00:24:44,115 --> 00:24:48,245
Take care of her, kid.

338
00:25:18,250 --> 00:25:20,115
Tsouti.

339
00:25:20,218 --> 00:25:22,015
Don't come near.

340
00:25:22,120 --> 00:25:24,145
- Tsouti.
- Don't come closer.

341
00:25:27,092 --> 00:25:28,184
It's me.

342
00:25:29,094 --> 00:25:30,254
Laishi.

343
00:25:31,096 --> 00:25:35,226
The one from your village.

344
00:25:37,269 --> 00:25:39,169
It's you?

345
00:25:59,224 --> 00:26:01,055
Are you Soo's regular client?

346
00:26:01,159 --> 00:26:06,028
I slipped in among the rebels.

347
00:26:06,097 --> 00:26:08,156
- So you are a rebel.
- No.

348
00:26:08,199 --> 00:26:10,224
All rebels deny they are.

349
00:26:11,002 --> 00:26:13,232
Soo said all rebels are womanizers.

350
00:26:14,005 --> 00:26:14,266
I'm not.

351
00:26:15,040 --> 00:26:17,008
They pushed me in.

352
00:26:17,075 --> 00:26:19,236
I wouldn't even go to the public bath.

353
00:26:20,078 --> 00:26:21,204
I'm afraid...

354
00:26:22,013 --> 00:26:23,173
You think you're a girl.

355
00:26:29,054 --> 00:26:33,081
I wish I were a boy and with a name.

356
00:26:38,063 --> 00:26:39,155
But your name is Tsouti.

357
00:26:39,230 --> 00:26:41,198
It only means

358
00:26:41,266 --> 00:26:43,131
to bring on a brother.

359
00:26:44,235 --> 00:26:46,100
A brother did come

360
00:26:46,171 --> 00:26:47,195
and it became too crowded.

361
00:26:47,272 --> 00:26:49,206
And my mum sold me to this place.

362
00:26:49,274 --> 00:26:53,142
For five coins, cheaper than a pig.

363
00:26:56,214 --> 00:26:58,273
Why didn't you tell me?

364
00:26:59,084 --> 00:27:00,244
I wanted to.

365
00:27:00,318 --> 00:27:02,218
But they told me you were hurt

366
00:27:02,287 --> 00:27:04,016
and locked up.

367
00:27:04,089 --> 00:27:05,113
The next day.

368
00:27:05,190 --> 00:27:07,215
I was sold to this place.

369
00:27:09,027 --> 00:27:11,222
Yes, where did it hurt?

370
00:27:13,264 --> 00:27:15,232
I...

371
00:27:15,300 --> 00:27:19,100
Never mind, you are well now.

372
00:27:19,270 --> 00:27:21,170
Don't feel sorry for me.

373
00:27:21,239 --> 00:27:26,040
I feel like a pig when I sleep with men.

374
00:27:26,111 --> 00:27:28,136
It's their loss.

375
00:27:28,179 --> 00:27:30,204
Don't I'll rescue you.

376
00:27:31,216 --> 00:27:33,207
I'll work and take care of you.

377
00:27:35,053 --> 00:27:37,146
It costs a lot to buy me out.

378
00:27:39,157 --> 00:27:40,215
I'll discuss it with my master.

379
00:27:40,291 --> 00:27:43,124
But you better.

380
00:27:43,194 --> 00:27:44,161
Not stay here.

381
00:27:44,229 --> 00:27:46,254
Don't you have to ask your wife?

382
00:27:49,167 --> 00:27:50,293
I don't have one.

383
00:27:51,136 --> 00:27:52,296
I don't have anything.

384
00:27:53,171 --> 00:27:56,231
I know all rebels are courageous.

385
00:27:57,175 --> 00:28:00,167
Hurry.

386
00:28:00,245 --> 00:28:01,269
Hurry up, please.

387
00:28:03,048 --> 00:28:03,275
Don't know, I'll tell you when there is.

388
00:28:04,082 --> 00:28:05,014
Where's the master?

389
00:28:05,083 --> 00:28:05,981
I said I didn't know.

390
00:28:06,051 --> 00:28:07,109
When will he be back?

391
00:28:07,185 --> 00:28:08,209
What a drag.

392
00:28:08,253 --> 00:28:10,153
How's Soo, was she good last night?

393
00:28:10,221 --> 00:28:11,245
They call her "One Stroke".

394
00:28:11,289 --> 00:28:13,018
And how's the virgin?

395
00:28:13,091 --> 00:28:14,080
- Tell us.
- Yes.

396
00:28:14,259 --> 00:28:18,218
Please see if someone's looking for me.

397
00:28:18,263 --> 00:28:21,164
Only you can go out and look.

398
00:28:21,232 --> 00:28:23,132
Is he crippled, can't he come in himself?

399
00:28:23,234 --> 00:28:25,099
Yeah.

400
00:28:25,136 --> 00:28:28,230
She's a girl, she can't come in.

401
00:28:30,008 --> 00:28:32,101
Oh! Smart kid.

402
00:28:32,177 --> 00:28:35,203
Yu Lan, someone's looking for you.

403
00:28:37,048 --> 00:28:37,275
Please wait.

404
00:28:38,049 --> 00:28:39,243
Yu Lan, they're looking for you.

405
00:28:42,187 --> 00:28:44,018
Are you Liu Yu Lan?

406
00:28:44,055 --> 00:28:45,079
Yes.

407
00:28:45,123 --> 00:28:47,216
Our boss isn't here.

408
00:28:47,292 --> 00:28:49,021
Yes...

409
00:28:49,060 --> 00:28:51,221
We are not here for your boss.

410
00:28:52,030 --> 00:28:53,156
Get away.

411
00:28:54,032 --> 00:28:58,128
General Lei sends for you.

412
00:28:58,203 --> 00:29:00,000
Some other time, can't make it today.

413
00:29:03,241 --> 00:29:05,175
General Lei is waiting.

414
00:29:07,212 --> 00:29:10,147
I don't know him.

415
00:29:10,248 --> 00:29:11,272
Thank him for me.

416
00:29:12,016 --> 00:29:13,074
Yes, yes.

417
00:29:20,091 --> 00:29:21,183
Let's go.

418
00:29:30,135 --> 00:29:32,000
Tea, master.

419
00:29:32,237 --> 00:29:35,035
At least you can delay them
till I come back.

420
00:29:35,106 --> 00:29:36,038
They have guns.

421
00:29:37,041 --> 00:29:40,010
So you were afraid. We have sabers.

422
00:29:40,078 --> 00:29:42,012
Was it a plot or you were scared?

423
00:29:42,080 --> 00:29:43,069
Can't even protect.

424
00:29:43,148 --> 00:29:44,115
A member of your troop.

425
00:29:44,182 --> 00:29:46,082
How can I depend on you in the future?

426
00:29:46,151 --> 00:29:47,175
What are you doing here?

427
00:29:47,252 --> 00:29:50,085
I'm looking for Laishi.

428
00:29:50,188 --> 00:29:52,088
The show's over, nobody's around.

429
00:29:52,157 --> 00:29:54,022
Laishi asked me to come.

430
00:29:54,092 --> 00:29:55,184
Send her away.

431
00:29:55,226 --> 00:29:58,218
Please take me to him.

432
00:29:58,296 --> 00:30:00,264
He asked me to come.

433
00:30:01,032 --> 00:30:02,226
Wait a minute.

434
00:30:03,234 --> 00:30:06,169
What do you want him for?
I'm his teacher.

435
00:30:09,040 --> 00:30:10,200
Are you running away?

436
00:30:12,277 --> 00:30:14,211
Go back, it's alright.

437
00:30:14,279 --> 00:30:17,112
Relax, I brought Laishi up with me.

438
00:30:17,182 --> 00:30:19,207
He treats me like his father.

439
00:30:19,284 --> 00:30:22,253
Is he here? He asked me to come.

440
00:30:23,288 --> 00:30:26,121
He's in trouble.
The general took him away.

441
00:30:26,191 --> 00:30:29,024
Has he been discovered?

442
00:30:29,160 --> 00:30:31,185
You know everything.

443
00:30:33,198 --> 00:30:35,291
I'm the only one who knows.

444
00:30:36,067 --> 00:30:37,091
Poor kid.

445
00:30:37,135 --> 00:30:39,228
He always keeps quiet.

446
00:30:39,270 --> 00:30:41,170
Has to be extra careful going to toilets.

447
00:30:41,239 --> 00:30:43,264
Or change, or go take a bath.

448
00:30:44,042 --> 00:30:45,202
That gets him no friends.

449
00:30:45,276 --> 00:30:49,007
That's why he denied it
when I made a guess.

450
00:30:49,080 --> 00:30:51,071
You're only guessing?

451
00:30:51,115 --> 00:30:53,174
Not really. I grew up with him.

452
00:30:53,251 --> 00:30:57,187
And bumped into each other last night.

453
00:30:58,056 --> 00:31:00,047
And found out that?

454
00:31:00,124 --> 00:31:01,250
He denied it all along.

455
00:31:02,060 --> 00:31:03,186
But call it a girl's intuition.

456
00:31:03,261 --> 00:31:05,195
Why did he ask you here?

457
00:31:07,131 --> 00:31:09,122
To live with him.

458
00:31:09,200 --> 00:31:13,102
I've been thinking, he's a nice person.

459
00:31:13,171 --> 00:31:15,071
I'll stay with him for life.

460
00:31:16,040 --> 00:31:18,235
Are you sure
that's more than being friends.

461
00:31:19,010 --> 00:31:20,272
It is for life...

462
00:31:21,045 --> 00:31:22,171
I understand.

463
00:31:22,247 --> 00:31:24,112
I'll cope with it.

464
00:31:24,148 --> 00:31:26,116
I won't ask.

465
00:31:26,184 --> 00:31:28,015
I'll keep his secrets.

466
00:31:28,052 --> 00:31:29,986
It's a matter of compromising.

467
00:31:30,088 --> 00:31:31,248
We'll be happy.

468
00:31:32,090 --> 00:31:34,183
Luck little devil.

469
00:31:36,060 --> 00:31:37,186
Is he in danger?

470
00:31:37,228 --> 00:31:40,129
Not too serious. It might hurt a bit.

471
00:31:40,198 --> 00:31:42,166
I wish I were here.

472
00:31:42,233 --> 00:31:44,224
You are both...

473
00:31:44,302 --> 00:31:46,167
Just Laishi, not me.

474
00:31:46,204 --> 00:31:49,071
You all deny it.

475
00:31:49,107 --> 00:31:50,131
So I am.

476
00:31:50,208 --> 00:31:51,175
See, I am right.

477
00:31:51,242 --> 00:31:53,233
Alright, alright.

478
00:32:12,096 --> 00:32:13,222
Stop.

479
00:32:14,098 --> 00:32:14,996
Don't move.

480
00:32:15,099 --> 00:32:16,157
Are you crazy?

481
00:32:16,234 --> 00:32:18,259
Be nice, they're Laishi's escorts.

482
00:32:19,037 --> 00:32:19,264
We've got sabers.

483
00:32:20,038 --> 00:32:21,096
So what? You stupid.

484
00:32:22,006 --> 00:32:23,166
Sorry, they're hot-tempered.

485
00:32:23,274 --> 00:32:25,139
We won't delay you any longer.

486
00:32:25,243 --> 00:32:29,202
General Lei sends a message.

487
00:32:29,280 --> 00:32:30,269
What's that?

488
00:32:31,049 --> 00:32:32,038
He's going to marry Yu Lan.

489
00:32:32,116 --> 00:32:35,051
Tomorrow.

490
00:32:39,290 --> 00:32:41,121
This is the wedding token.

491
00:32:50,034 --> 00:32:51,194
Go pack up.

492
00:32:51,269 --> 00:32:53,100
And see me later.

493
00:32:53,271 --> 00:32:55,102
Go.

494
00:32:59,077 --> 00:33:00,066
Did the beast?

495
00:33:00,111 --> 00:33:02,272
- No.
- Yours.

496
00:33:06,050 --> 00:33:08,211
What if he sends for me tomorrow?

497
00:33:10,088 --> 00:33:12,022
Tsouti's waiting for you inside.

498
00:33:12,123 --> 00:33:13,249
Take her to your folks
first thing tomorrow.

499
00:33:14,025 --> 00:33:16,118
General Lei won't be able to find you.

500
00:33:17,061 --> 00:33:20,121
But what about you, master?

501
00:33:20,164 --> 00:33:23,065
You want to live with Lei for life?

502
00:33:23,234 --> 00:33:24,166
Go.

503
00:33:24,235 --> 00:33:27,102
Tsouti is a good girl.

504
00:33:28,006 --> 00:33:30,167
Don't act like a woman,
she won't like it.

505
00:33:30,274 --> 00:33:32,174
Go.

506
00:33:32,276 --> 00:33:34,210
Go ahead.

507
00:33:49,260 --> 00:33:51,160
How's it?

508
00:33:54,232 --> 00:33:56,063
Where does it hurt?

509
00:33:56,167 --> 00:33:57,225
I...

510
00:34:01,172 --> 00:34:02,196
- They burned you with fire.
- No.

511
00:34:02,273 --> 00:34:04,002
- Burned you with cigarettes.
- No.

512
00:34:04,042 --> 00:34:05,031
- Clamped your fingers.
- No.

513
00:34:05,109 --> 00:34:06,235
- Hung you upside down.
- No.

514
00:34:07,278 --> 00:34:09,143
I don't know what to tell you.

515
00:34:09,247 --> 00:34:10,236
The truth of course.

516
00:34:11,049 --> 00:34:12,073
Don't tell me.

517
00:34:12,116 --> 00:34:14,050
You need violin music.

518
00:34:16,054 --> 00:34:18,215
I...

519
00:34:18,289 --> 00:34:20,018
What don't girls like?

520
00:34:20,091 --> 00:34:21,149
Get it out.

521
00:34:23,027 --> 00:34:26,292
I'm leaving, I want you to come with me.

522
00:34:29,200 --> 00:34:30,224
Special mission.

523
00:34:30,268 --> 00:34:32,133
No.

524
00:34:32,203 --> 00:34:34,034
Military secret, can't you tell?

525
00:34:34,072 --> 00:34:35,232
No.

526
00:34:38,242 --> 00:34:40,210
I know you won't tell.

527
00:34:40,278 --> 00:34:42,143
Never mind, go back to the old home.

528
00:34:42,246 --> 00:34:45,079
Tsouti is so nice.
She'll keep the secret.

529
00:34:45,149 --> 00:34:47,140
Tell me.

530
00:34:47,218 --> 00:34:49,152
If he mistreats you.

531
00:34:51,089 --> 00:34:54,217
Take care, master, we're going.

532
00:35:00,131 --> 00:35:03,100
Laishi, you're forgotten your thing.

533
00:35:03,167 --> 00:35:04,293
Thing?

534
00:35:06,070 --> 00:35:08,129
Why didn't you mention this?

535
00:35:10,241 --> 00:35:11,173
What is it?

536
00:35:11,242 --> 00:35:13,107
That's his thing.

537
00:35:25,022 --> 00:35:26,182
You're not a rebel.

538
00:35:26,290 --> 00:35:28,155
I'm a eunuch.

539
00:35:39,036 --> 00:35:40,196
I didn't mean to lie.

540
00:35:40,271 --> 00:35:44,037
I'm a good man,
no fooling around, no gambling.

541
00:35:45,176 --> 00:35:46,234
You'd said you didn't mind.

542
00:35:48,012 --> 00:35:50,242
Go away, you two freaks.

543
00:35:51,015 --> 00:35:52,073
I?

544
00:36:08,065 --> 00:36:11,228
She changes her mind. Go alone.

545
00:36:15,273 --> 00:36:17,207
I'm a eunuch.

546
00:36:17,275 --> 00:36:20,244
I'll be treated as a freak.

547
00:36:23,181 --> 00:36:26,082
Go to the Palace. You're safe there.

548
00:36:26,150 --> 00:36:28,175
No one will treat you like a freak there.

549
00:36:28,252 --> 00:36:31,016
But you told me not to go to the Palace.

550
00:36:31,088 --> 00:36:32,248
I didn't say that.

551
00:36:32,290 --> 00:36:35,054
Hold your head high

552
00:36:35,092 --> 00:36:36,992
be a proud eunuch.

553
00:36:37,061 --> 00:36:38,153
A eunuch has dignity too.

554
00:36:38,229 --> 00:36:43,132
Just like being an actor.

555
00:36:49,173 --> 00:36:50,231
My respect to you, sir.

556
00:36:50,274 --> 00:36:51,263
Master.

557
00:36:52,043 --> 00:36:53,203
Stand straight.

558
00:36:53,244 --> 00:36:55,144
Be proud, be a man.

559
00:36:55,213 --> 00:36:56,271
Yes.

560
00:36:57,048 --> 00:36:58,242
Is that how a eunuch would say it?

561
00:36:59,116 --> 00:37:00,276
Yes.

562
00:37:09,193 --> 00:37:12,026
- Be good.
- Yes.

563
00:37:13,130 --> 00:37:14,256
Go.

564
00:37:15,199 --> 00:37:17,099
Yes.

565
00:37:26,210 --> 00:37:30,044
Yesterday has left me irretrievably.

566
00:37:30,081 --> 00:37:33,175
Today weighs me down with worries.

567
00:37:33,251 --> 00:37:36,015
Send off those migratory birds.

568
00:37:36,053 --> 00:37:40,114
And sleep off the day in style.

569
00:38:01,045 --> 00:38:02,205
You are a rebel?

570
00:38:03,247 --> 00:38:04,179
Where's the rebel?

